"560","<TEXT>"
"561","Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm"
"562","To the Trustees and Shareholders of Putnam Global Income"
"563","Trust:"
"564","In planning and performing our audit of the financial"
"565","statements of Putnam Global Income Trust (the Fund) as of and"
"566","for the year ended October 31, 2017, in accordance with the"
"567","standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board"
"568","(United States), we considered the Funds internal control over"
"569","financial reporting, including controls over safeguarding"
"570","securities, as a basis for designing our auditing procedures"
"571","for the purpose of expressing our opinion on the financial"
"572","statements and to comply with the requirements of Form N-SAR,"
"573","but not for the purpose of expressing an opinion on the"
"574","effectiveness of the Funds internal control over financial"
"575","reporting.  Accordingly, we do not express an opinion on the"
"576","effectiveness of the Funds internal control over financial"
"577","reporting."
"578","The management of the Fund is responsible for establishing and"
"579","maintaining effective internal control over financial"
"580","reporting.  In fulfilling this responsibility, estimates and"
"581","judgments by management are required to assess the expected"
"582","benefits and related costs of controls.  A funds internal"
"583","control over financial reporting is a process designed to"
"584","provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of"
"585","financial reporting and the preparation of financial"
"586","statements for external purposes in accordance with generally"
"587","accepted accounting principles.  A funds internal control over"
"588","financial reporting includes those policies and procedures"
"589","that (1) pertain to the maintenance of records that, in"
"590","reasonable detail, accurately and fairly reflect the"
"591","transactions and dispositions of the assets of the fund; (2)"
"592","provide reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded as"
"593","necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in"
"594","accordance with generally accepted accounting principles, and"
"595","that receipts and expenditures of the fund are being made only"
"596","in accordance with authorizations of management and trustees"
"597","of the fund; and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding"
"598","prevention or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition,"
"599","use or disposition of a funds assets that could have a"
"600","material effect on the financial statements."
"601","Because of its inherent limitations, internal control over"
"602","financial reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements."
"603","Also, projections of any evaluation of effectiveness to future"
"604","periods are subject to the risk that controls may become"
"605","inadequate because of changes in conditions, or that the"
"606","degree of compliance with the policies or procedures may"
"607","deteriorate."
"608","A deficiency in internal control over financial reporting"
"609","exists when the design or operation of a control does not"
"610","allow management or employees, in the normal course of"
"611","performing their assigned functions, to prevent or detect"
"612","misstatements on a timely basis.  A material weakness is a"
"613","deficiency, or a combination of deficiencies, in internal"
"614","control over financial reporting, such that there is a"
"615","reasonable possibility that a material misstatement of the"
"616","Funds annual or interim financial statements will not be"
"617","prevented or detected on a timely basis."
"618","Our consideration of the Funds internal control over financial"
